	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
		"name": "MSAI — API Test Suite",
		"description": "## MSAI API Test Suite\n\nEnd-to-end API test collection for the MSAI event management platform.\n\n### Assumptions (Undocumented Endpoints)\n\nThe following assumptions were made about request/response shapes for endpoints without a provided contract:\n\n**POST /api/register**\n- Request: `{ \"name\": \"string\", \"email\": \"string\", \"password\": \"string\" }`\n- 201 Created: `{ \"message\": \"User registered successfully\", \"userId\": \"string\" }`\n- 400 Bad Request: `{ \"error\": \"string\" }` (missing/invalid fields)\n- 409 Conflict: `{ \"error\": \"Email already registered\" }` (duplicate registration)\n\n**GET /api/events**\n- No request body required; Authorization header with Bearer token.\n- 200 OK: `{ \"events\": [ { \"id\": \"string\", \"title\": \"string\", \"description\": \"string\", \"date\": \"ISO8601 string\", \"location\": \"string\", \"capacity\": number, \"registered\": number } ] }`\n- 401 Unauthorized: `{ \"error\": \"Unauthorized\" }`\n\n**POST /api/events/register**\n- Request: `{ \"eventId\": \"string\" }`; Authorization header with Bearer token.\n- 200 OK: `{ \"message\": \"Successfully registered for event\", \"registrationId\": \"string\" }`\n- 400 Bad Request: `{ \"error\": \"string\" }` (missing eventId)\n- 401 Unauthorized: `{ \"error\": \"Unauthorized\" }`\n- 409 Conflict: `{ \"error\": \"Already registered for this event\" }` (duplicate)\n- 422 Unprocessable Entity: `{ \"error\": \"Event is full\" }` (capacity reached)\n\n**POST /api/payment**\n- Request: `{ \"registrationId\": \"string\", \"amount\": number, \"currency\": \"string\", \"paymentMethod\": \"string\" }`; Authorization header with Bearer token.\n- 200 OK: `{ \"message\": \"Payment successful\", \"transactionId\": \"string\" }`\n- 400 Bad Request: `{ \"error\": \"string\" }` (missing/invalid fields)\n- 401 Unauthorized: `{ \"error\": \"Unauthorized\" }`\n- 422 Unprocessable Entity: `{ \"error\": \"Invalid amount\" }` (zero/negative amount)\n\n**GET /api/registrations**\n- No request body; Authorization header with Bearer token.\n- 200 OK: `{ \"registrations\": [ { \"registrationId\": \"string\", \"eventId\": \"string\", \"eventTitle\": \"string\", \"registeredAt\": \"ISO8601 string\", \"paymentStatus\": \"string\" } ] }`\n- 401 Unauthorized: `{ \"error\": \"Unauthorized\" }`\n\n### Token Chaining\nThe Login (Happy Path) request captures the JWT token from the response and stores it in the `token` environment variable. All subsequent authenticated requests reference `{{token}}` in their Authorization header — no hardcoded tokens anywhere.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Register",
			"description": "POST /api/register — User registration endpoint.",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Register — Happy Path",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 201 Created', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response contains userId', function () {",
									"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('userId');",
									"    pm.expect(typeof jsonData.userId).to.equal('string');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response contains success message', function () {",
									"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('message');",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.message).to.include('registered');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response time is below 2000ms', function () {",
									"    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(2000);",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"Test User\",\n    \"email\": \"{{register_email}}\",\n    \"password\": \"SecurePass123!\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/register",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "register"]
						},
						"description": "Registers a new user with valid name, email, and password."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Register — Missing Required Field",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 400 Bad Request', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(400);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response contains error message', function () {",
									"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('error');",
									"    pm.expect(typeof jsonData.error).to.equal('string');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response time is below 2000ms', function () {",
									"    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(2000);",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"Test User\",\n    \"email\": \"missing_password@example.com\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/register",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "register"]
						},
						"description": "Attempts registration with the password field omitted. Expects 400."
					},
					"response": []
				},
				{
					"name": "Register — Duplicate Email",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"pm.test('Status code is 409 Conflict', function () {",
									"    pm.response.to.have.status(409);",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response indicates duplicate registration', function () {",
									"    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('error');",
									"    pm.expect(jsonData.error.toLowerCase()).to.include('already');",
									"});",
									"",
									"pm.test('Response time is below 2000ms', function () {",
									"    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(2000);",
									"});"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"Test User\",\n    \"email\": \"{{register_email}}\",\n    \"password\": \"SecurePass123!\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{base_url}}/api/register",
							"host": ["{{base_url}}"],
							"path": ["api", "register"]
						},
						"description": "Attempts to register with the same email used in the happy-path request. Expects 409 Conflict."
					},
					"response": []
				}
			]
